        "creation_date": 1550476002,
        "answer_count": 5,
        "title": "Java, Caused by: java.io.IOException: error=2, No such file or directory",
        "body": "<pre><code>java.io.IOException: Cannot run program \"yarn\": error=2, No such file or directory\n    at java.lang.ProcessBuilder.start(ProcessBuilder.java:1048)\n    at java.lang.Runtime.exec(Runtime.java:620)\n    at java.lang.Runtime.exec(Runtime.java:450)\n    at java.lang.Runtime.exec(Runtime.java:347)\n    at com.Main.main(Main.java:32)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Hi there, I have a weird problem when execute a command using Java. I used the following code to run a command, if I run <code>mkdir testFolder<\/code>, the program run successful, but if I changed the command like <code>yarn -v<\/code>\nthen error happen.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>try {\n    Process process = Runtime.getRuntime().exec(\"yarn -v\");//, null, new File(\"/Users/macos/Desktop/TestProj/\"));\n} catch (IOException ex) {\n    ex.printStackTrace();\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>P/s: In debug mode: IntelliJ could run above code, but Netbeans failed.<\/p>\n\n<p>In production mode (jar file): IntelliJ failed too.<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>Edit 2:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>  MACs-MacBook-Pro:~ macos$ which pwd\n    /bin/pwd\n    MACs-MacBook-Pro:~ macos$ which mkdir\n    /bin/mkdir\n    MACs-MacBook-Pro:~ macos$ which java\n    /usr/bin/java\n    MACs-MacBook-Pro:~ macos$ which yarn\n    /usr/local/bin/yarn\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I found that if I run a command that is in <code>/bin<\/code> or <code>/usr/bin<\/code>, the code run ok (pwd, mkdir, java -version ...), but yarn is in <code>/usr/local/bin/<\/code>, so it didn't work, and I still don't know how to fix.<\/p>\n",
